Machine Learning on OS X 10.11.6
--------------------------------
Here are the commands I ran on my Macbook Pro Retina 13.
I’ve installed both Python2.7 and Python3.


Installing Python 2.7
---------------------
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)”
brew update
brew install python
xcode-select —install
pip install --upgrade pip setuptools
pip install numpy pandas matplotlib jupyter scikit-learn scipy
brew linkapps python

Installing python 3
-------------------
/usr/bin/ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
brew update
brew install python3
brew tap Homebrew/python
brew install numpy --with-python3
brew install matplotlib --with-python3
pip3 install pandas jupyter scikit-learn scipy